Energy Minister Jeff Radebe has reappointed Jacob Modise, Maleho Nkomo and Fungai Sibanda as part-time regulator members of the National Energy Regulator of South Africa (Nersa). Modise was reappointed as Nersa chairperson and Nkomo as deputy chairperson. Nomfundo Maseti has been appointed as a full-time member, primarily responsible for piped gas regulation and electricity regulation for 12 months, or until a permanent appointment is made.